ic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Marus Seru</span><hr size=1> The exp is pretty good here, I'd rather level here than loio. I came here at 25 and it's pretty easy with a focused fire pet. I set up my camp behind the white sand and just pull wandering stuff to me, kind of like orc high way in Oasis. One malise, two shocks and the mob is down by then. The fire pet is a killing machine here, he can basically solo a dark blue without any help at all. I sometimes get adds or unexpected mobs when the Zelniaks see me but the fire pet keeps me safe. The only thing you have to watch out for are the Zelniaks and their large aggro radius. Otherwise, this zone is pretty good. I checked Allakhazam and it's definitely able to support a mage 24-29.  <p><img src="http://yomad.freewebspace.com/YoMaDsig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uno1bri.showPublicProfile?language=EN>No1Bri</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(4/3/02 8:16:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels2428.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=46.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   NICE!!!!</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the info, great place.  If anyone is sick of LOIO Come here!!!! Its is 10 times better then LOIO, its not crowded, and most things arnt KOS.<br>
<br>
<br>
Dunker Level 27 Mage -Bristlebane-<br>
Ibiar Level 47 Enchanter -Bristlebane- <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=yomad>YoMaD</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#333333>(4/4/02 12:04:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels2428.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=46.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: NICE!!!!</span><hr size=1> Damn I see An Ancient Zelniak and he's white to me at 27 so I give him a try. He hits for 80. Well I survived but I had to chain heal/nuke. Didn't drop anything but I got almost a blue of exp. Never pull him if you only have 1-2 bubs of mana like I usually do. I was lucky I had about 70%. I eventually got tired of solo'ing and joined a group. Constant pulls give good exp in groups here. We usually stuck to the middle of the two rocks to the left of netherbian zone, the house thing. The casters all sat on the rocks above and we had almost no down time. One time the puller got lost and when we retrieved him he had 9-10 mobs, the 2 zelniaks were killed by the guards and it was pretty cool to take on all of those instead of single/double pulls. This is a definite zone for mid-upper twenties. Some things are still dark blue at 30. I just hope I don't see 70+ people in this zone soon when it gets popular.<br>
<br>
Some additional notes: Everything in this zone will con indifferent besides the zelniaks so pulling is pretty safe unless you get into the long aggro range of the zelniaks. One downside is no coin drops. Most of the time there are words and runes though so you can just sell that.  <p><img src="http://yomad.freewebspace.com/YoMaDsig.jpg"></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=yomad>YoMaD</A> at: 4/4/02 12:06:09 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uteamnoir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>teamnoir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#333333>(4/6/02 11:12:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels2428.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=46.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: NICE!!!!</span><hr size=1> I levelled my beastlord here.  Cool zone; squat for drops.<br>
<br>
You also need to watch for lightcrawlers.  They are about the biggest things in the zone at times and they move FAST.  Faster than sow.  Both lightcrawlers and zelniaks aggro, and from quite a distance.  However, the guards will kill either for you, which helps somewhat.<br>
<br>
Also try hunting near sseru zone.<br>
<br>
Aanni <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uquarto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quarto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(9/19/02 7:13:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels2428.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=46.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.forumplanet.com/iconcommon/default/sets/customavatar/593597-icon.gif  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Marus Seru</span><hr size=1> Bringing up my mage here. Great place to solo, dont think you will get rich here. <br>
My technique is to use a focus fire and pull a rockhopper from far out. Rest while pet is killing, maybe throw in a nuke to speed things up. As hopper is in his death thrawls, take off after another. I can usually get 3-4 of these in a row and then ill go sit by the wall (90% safe) and find something to do for 10 minutes while I med and pet heals. <br>
Got a stack of rockhopper hides pretty quickly this way, not sure how well they sell in bazaar. <br>
Was able to do yellow stonegrabbers this way as well (with a fire pet), but almost got killed when I pulled a yellow beetle. These things hit VERY hard and lil' Flamey couldnt keep up at all.<br>
Less than a bub to 28 at the moment, and this place should carry me to 30 easily.<br>
Great place 24+!!! Only 9 people in zone prime time last night....abundant pulls.......MUCH better than LOIO!! <p><img src=http://coffeehouseforwriters.com/images/Quarto.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utangting.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TangTing</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#333333>(9/19/02 11:18:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels2428.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=46.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Yes, great zone</span><hr size=1> I took Marus Seru from about 27 to 33 or so.  From 33 alternated between Marus and Golras, mostly golras to 38. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nimmamen>Nimmamen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(12/25/02 6:50:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels2428.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=46.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   love this zone</span><hr size=1> ah i loved this zone, i dinged 25,26,27,28,29 here in a few days.  Used this combo<br>
lvl 24 earth pet<br>
burnout (always)<br>
1 spear of warding<br>
Elemental Defender (use shield since pet hardly duel wields and imho the 14dmg boost and 10ac boost is more useful then the low chance of an ATTEMPT to hit with 2nd weapon <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
summoned leather<br>
<br>
pick out a mob like the stonegrabbers (i personally hate those stupid grayhoppers cause they train like mad and made me gate a few times <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
ds your pet, nuke the mob (perferablly with bolt for the delayed hit) run to a safer location, and hit pet attack before he reaches you, 99% of the time pet will take him.  After that swap heals and nukes, i usally nuked 3 times for 60% of the dmg.  Also, try to pick up a kei in nexus, speeds this up much faster <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  If you get trained gate out. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eciypse>EcIypse</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.myoswego.net/~mojoteq/pics/17anidot5c.gif " BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(1/8/03 10:53:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels2428.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=46.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: love this zone</span><hr size=1> Uh, Nim, you can give the pet a summoned fang, and the elemental defender, and it will equip it in the back slot... also try giving it the summoned focus items. <p>      <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Love is the answer; but while you're waiting for the answer, sex raises some pretty good questions.&quot; (Woody Allen) </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elladin>Elladin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#333333>(2/19/03 4:40:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels2428.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=46.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: love this zone</span><hr size=1> Wow, I know this froum is beggining to sound like a love fest, but all of you are absolutely correct. I went into MSeru last nite for the first time. OMG, the exp rocks! I am using my earth pet (LOL my research sucks so bad I havent gotten any of my other '24' pet spells yet, plus Words of Dimension are hard to find). I equip my earth pet with :<br>
<br>
spear of warding<br>
elemental defender<br>
phantom leather (pieces given separately) <br>
Burnout I<br>
Fire Shield.<br>
<br>
I used malise and rain of blades. The yellow mobs sometimes resist the spells, but it is rare. I went in last nite with about 1.5 yellow bubs into 25. I was invited into a grp immediately. I fought for about 2 hrs in the grp and dinged 26 before the grp broke up. After going to the nexus for a fresh C3, I terturned for about an hour and got 2.5 yellow bubs into 26. The only time I came close to dying, I had pulled a stonegrabber and while I was fighting it, I was aggroed by a zelniak and a lightcrawler. As I was fighting the other two, my pet came and took aggro which allowed me to run to the guards.<br>
<br>
Any advice from my older brothers and sisters here will be greatly appreciated, but nonetheless, I think I have found my new home for awhile.<br>
<br>
Aeedar Incantus<br>
Human mage of the 26th season<br>
Luclin  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels2428.showPrevMessage?topicID=46.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels2428.showNextMessage?topicID=46.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels2428.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=46.topic&index=8><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels2428.threadControl?topicID=46.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels2428.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=46.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels2428.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=46.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="themagicianstowerannouncements">Administration<option value="themagicianstowergeneral">General<option value="themagicianstowerfrm32">Class Balance<option value="themagicianstowerfrm45">User Interface<option value="themagicianstowerspells">Spells<option value="themagicianstowerequipmentandquests">Quests<option value="themagicianstowerfrm28">Equipment<option value="themagicianstowerfrm29">Magician Pets<option value="themagicianstowe